Covered only with leaves and mud that makes you drown. Place of the wild life fauna. :-)

title: How to tell if you have A.D.D #shorts
comments:
The cons to ADD is not able to concentrate on one thought for any length of time, the inability to get stuck into a job you must get done, and having so many distractions.

The pros to ADD is that you can think laterally. Where other people can only see narrowly along one line, ADD allows those people to see different connections to particular situations. Often making for humourous quick witted conversations or jokes, and being able to, on the fly, figure out particular issues that can have multiple solutions. ADD is better suited to work which requires more creativity or work which requires more movement because it's also the movement which stimulates attention to the job concerned.

However, I who have had ADD since I was little, do know that one of the reasons I do not see items I am searching for which are in front of me is because although I am looking at it, my mind is already on the next possible place it could be.

Like with any mental state, it has its pros and cons.
